# Project Rules

## Architecture
- Monorepo structure with pnpm workspaces
- apps/: Executable/deployable units (api, desktop, landing)
- packages/: Shared code (types, config, utils)

## Tech Stack
- Desktop: Electron + React + TypeScript
- API: Express + Prisma + PostgreSQL
- Landing: Next.js
- Email: Nodemailer

## Coding Standards
- TypeScript strict mode
- File size limit: ~2000 characters
- One responsibility per file/function
- English for code, Korean allowed in comments only
- No emojis in code/logs/commits

## Error Handling
- Use AppError class from @ppop/utils
- Wrap external errors with domain errors
- No console.log for debugging (use logger)

## Environment
- DEV: Single .env file
- PROD: GitHub Environment variables

## Commands (from root)
- pnpm dev - Run all apps
- pnpm build - Build all apps
- pnpm clean - Clean artifacts
- pnpm version:patch - Release new version

## CI/CD
- Trigger: git push --tags
- Builds: exe (Windows), dmg (macOS)
- Deploy: Railway (API, Landing)
